<p>Tobias, M.M. &amp; C.C. Myles. 2021. “Wine, culture, and environment: A study of the Sierra (Nevada) Foothills American Viticultural Area” in <em>Handbook of Wine and Culture</em>, Tim Unwin, ed. Routledge. (In progress)</p>

<p>Cantu, et al. 2021. <a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S030881462031582X">Investigating the impact of regionality on the sensorial and chemical aging characteristics of Pinot noir grown throughout the U.S. West coast.</a>.  <em>Food Chemistry</em> 337(2021).</p>

<p>Myles, C.C., M.M. Tobias, &amp; I. McKinnon. 2020. “‘A big fish in a small pond’: How Arizona wine country was made” in <a href="https://www.routledge.com/Agritourism-Wine-Tourism-and-Craft-Beer-Tourism-Local-Responses-to-Peripherality/Pezzi-Faggian-Reid/p/book/9781138614413"><em>Agritourism, Wine Tourism, Craft Beer Tourism: Local Responses to peripherality through tourism niches.</em></a>  Maria Giulia Pezzi (GSSI), Alessandra Faggian (GSSI), Neil Reid (University of Toledo, OH), eds.</p>

<p>2018 <a href="https://www.ucop.edu/information-technology-services/initiatives/sautter-award-program/award-winners-and-applications/2018.html">Sautter Award</a> - Silver - for Innovation in Information Technologies, awarded by the University of California Office of the President.</p>

